---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Tokyo Mix Style</h1>
			<p>
				Japanese fashion has always known how to do "less, but better." Tokyo Mix Style is about
				pairing that philosophy — clean basics from brands like UNIQLO and Muji — with the
				character and sustainability of secondhand pieces. The result is a wardrobe that feels
				considered, not trend-chasing, and a lot more interesting than buying everything new.
			</p>
			<p>
				This is a small, slow-growing blog. New guides go up roughly once a week, focused on
				realistic outfit combinations, capsule wardrobe building, and honest comparisons of the
				Japanese brands most people outside Japan have heard of but aren't sure how to wear.
			</p>
			<p>
				Start with the <a href="/blog">latest posts</a>, or read more about
				<a href="/about">why this site exists</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
